<item>
            <title>[LU-5693] LNET configuration for dual ib port/ dual rail</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5693</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Dear Team,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;IB-Switch-1 ib0  ( All IB0 port connected to this switch only) 192.168.2.*&lt;br/&gt;
IB-Switch-2 ib1  ( All IB1 port connected to this switch only) 192.168.3.*&lt;br/&gt;
Both the IB switch are physically separated.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;IO1 ibo 192.168.2.1&lt;br/&gt;
IO1 ib1 192.168.3.1&lt;br/&gt;
IO2 ib0 192.168.2.2&lt;br/&gt;
IO2 ib1 192.168.3.2&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Client1 ibo 192.168.2.10&lt;br/&gt;
Client1 ib1 192.168.3.10&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Goal:- Switch level fail-over&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As per the above details we need to configure LNET in such a way if 1 IB switch fail, then the communication should establish from 2 IB switch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please guide us to archive the goal &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thank You&lt;br/&gt;
Atul Yadav&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Centos 6.5 &lt;br/&gt;
mellanox 2 switch&lt;br/&gt;
Dell server with 2 IB ports </environment>
